    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/dask-array-materialization-and-collection/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "sq.im.calculate_image_features(adata, img, features=<list>, spot_scale=<float>, scale=<float>, key_added=<str>)... Feature extraction can be parallelized by providing n_jobs (see Supplementary Fig. 1). The calculated feature matrix is stored in adata[key].",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms im.calculate_image_features stores features in AnnData and mentions lazy loading via Dask for image handling (passage 5: 'lazy loading, image tiling and multiprocessing'), but does not explicitly document the workflow of materializing lazy dask arrays into obsm/obsp/var slots or the explicit .compute() pattern. The paper describes lazy loading of images themselves, not lazy feature arrays awaiting materialization.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "dask-array-materialization-and-collection",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Materialize and collect lazy dask arrays into concrete AnnData object slots (obsm, obsp, var) after lazy feature extraction via im.calculate_image_features, ensuring intermediate computations remain deferred until explicitly triggered.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:08:51.212885+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/dask-array-materialization-and-collection/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Following standard image-based profiling techniques, Squidpy implements a pipeline based on Dask Image and Scikit-image for preprocessing and segmenting images, extracting morphological, texture and deep-learning-powered features (Fig. 3a). To enable efficient processing of very large images, this pipeline utilizes lazy loading, image tiling and multiprocessing.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Squidpy provides im.calculate_image_features and ImageContainer with lazy loading via Dask, but the lazy loading refers to image I/O (on-disk/in-memory switch), not lazy feature arrays. The feature extraction itself is not explicitly described as returning lazy dask arrays awaiting .compute().",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "dask-array-materialization-and-collection",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Squidpy provides im.calculate_image_features and ImageContainer APIs for lazy image feature extraction",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:08:51.212885+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/dask-array-materialization-and-collection/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Squidpy is built on top of Scanpy and Anndata and it relies on several scientific computing libraries in Python, such as Scikit-image, Napari and Dask. To enable efficient processing of very large images, this pipeline utilizes lazy loading, image tiling and multiprocessing (Supplementary Fig. 1b). On-disk files are loaded lazily using dask, meaning content is only read in memory when requested.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Dask is a core dependency for lazy evaluation and deferred computation in Squidpy's image processing pipeline.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "dask-array-materialization-and-collection",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "dask enables lazy array computation, task graphs, and deferred evaluation; provides .compute() for materialization",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:08:51.212885+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/dask-array-materialization-and-collection/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Squidpy is built on top of Scanpy and Anndata and... The calculated feature matrix is stored in adata[key]. This image feature matrix can then be used in any single-cell analysis workflow, just like the gene matrix.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms AnnData is the storage container for features extracted by Squidpy, though specific slot names (obsm, obsp, var) are not explicitly named in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "dask-array-materialization-and-collection",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "anndata defines AnnData object slots (obsm, obsp, var) where materialized features are stored",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:08:51.212885+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/dask-array-materialization-and-collection/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Squidpy is built on top of Scanpy and Anndata and it relies on several scientific computing libraries in Python... Its modularity makes it suitable to be interfaced with a variety of additional tools in the Python data science and machine-learning ecosystem... as well as several single-cell data analysis packages.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Squidpy is built on Scanpy and integrates with the single-cell analysis ecosystem, though the specific role in feature storage is not detailed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "dask-array-materialization-and-collection",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "scanpy provides ecosystem utilities for spatial analysis that integrate with squidpy feature storage",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:08:51.212885+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/dask-array-materialization-and-collection/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Squidpy introduces a new data object, the ImageContainer, which efficiently stores the image with an on-disk/in-memory switch based on xArray and Dask. This object provides a general mapping between pixel coordinates and molecular profiles, enabling analysts to relate image-level observations to omics measurements.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes lazy image I/O and feature extraction pipelines, but does not explicitly document a workflow for materializing lazy feature arrays into AnnData slots. The card's specific focus on dask array materialization (.compute()) and explicit control of when computation is triggered is not addressed in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "dask-array-materialization-and-collection",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "bridges lazy image feature computation with persistent storage in spatial omics workflows",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:08:51.212885+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/euclidean-distance-computation-approximation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For a fixed number of the closest spots for each spot, it leverages the k-nearest neighbors search from Scikit-learn49 and n_neigh must be used to set the number of neighbors. sq.gr.spatial_neighbors(adata, coord_type=\"generic\", n_neigh=<int>)",
      "asbval:note": "Paper implements k-nearest neighbor graph construction but uses Scikit-learn's k-nearest neighbors search, not pynndescent. The functional goal (k-NN graph from spatial coordinates) is present, but the specific tool (pynndescent) is not mentioned anywhere in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "euclidean-distance-computation-approximation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Approximate k-nearest neighbor graph construction using Euclidean distance metrics via the pynndescent library integrated into GraphBuilderCSR subclasses",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:09:07.425610+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/euclidean-distance-computation-approximation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Squidpy provides efficient infrastructure and numerous analysis methods that allow to efficiently store, manipulate and interactively visualize spatial omics data... Spatial proximity is encoded in spatial graphs, which require flexibility to support the variety of neighborhood metrics that spatial data types and users may require.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly addresses scalable nearest-neighbor discovery for spatial omics workflows.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "euclidean-distance-computation-approximation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "scalable nearest-neighbor discovery for spatial coordinate data in spatial omics workflows",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
