    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/graph-builder-subclassing-squidpy/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Squidpy introduces two main data representations to manage and store spatial omics data in a technology-agnostic way: a neighborhood graph from spatial coordinates and large-source tissue images acquired in spatial omics data (Fig. 1b)... Spatial proximity is encoded in spatial graphs, which require flexibility to support the variety of neighborhood metrics that spatial data types and users may require.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Squidpy builds spatial graphs from coordinates and supports flexible neighborhood metrics (k-NN, radius, Delaunay). However, paper does not mention a class named 'GraphBuilderCSR' or pynndescent integration. Paper uses Scikit-learn's k-nearest neighbors and Delaunay triangulation (scipy), not pynndescent. The task card proposes a custom subclassing pattern not documented in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "graph-builder-subclassing-squidpy",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Subclass Squidpy's GraphBuilderCSR to integrate a custom nearest-neighbor backend (such as pynndescent) for approximate k-NN graph construction on spatial coordinates.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:09:25.345306+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/graph-builder-subclassing-squidpy/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The function builds a spatial graph and saves its adjacency and weighted adjacency matrices to adata.obsp['spatial_connectivities'] in either Numpy or Scipy sparse arrays. The weights of the weighted adjacency matrix are distances in the case of coord_type = 'generic' and ordinal numbers of hexagonal rings in the case of coord_type = 'grid'. Together with the connectivities, we also provide a sparse adjacency matrix of distances, saved in adata.obsp['spatial_distances']",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly confirms sparse adjacency and distance matrices are core to Squidpy's spatial graph infrastructure and are used for downstream spatial statistics.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "graph-builder-subclassing-squidpy",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill enables scalable construction of sparse adjacency and distance matrices from coordinate data, essential for downstream spatial statistics and feature extraction in spatial omics workflows.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:09:25.345306+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/graph-builder-subclassing-squidpy/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "pynndescent is not mentioned anywhere in the paper. Squidpy uses Scikit-learn's k-nearest neighbors (sq.gr.spatial_neighbors with n_neigh parameter) and scipy.spatial for Delaunay triangulation, not pynndescent.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
