    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/graph-builder-subclassing-squidpy/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Spatial proximity is encoded in spatial graphs, which require flexibility to support the variety of neighborhood metrics that spatial data types and users may require. For instance, in Spatial Transcriptomics (ST, Visium and DBit-seq), a node is a spot and a neighborhood set can be defined by a fixed number of adjacent spots (square or hexagonal grid; Fig. 2a), whereas in imaging-based molecular data (seqFISH, MERFISH, Imaging Mass Cytometry, CyCif, 4i and Spatial Metabolomics; Fig. 2a), a node can be defined as a cell (or pixel) and a neighborhood set can also be chosen based on a fixed radius (expressed in spatial units) from the centroid of each observation. Alternatively, other approaches, such as Euclidean distance or Delaunay triangulation, can be utilized to build the neighbor graph.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms spatial molecular data in AnnData, k-NN graph construction, and spatial statistics use cases. However, paper does not mention pynndescent or approximate-NN libraries; it uses Scikit-learn's k-nearest neighbors and Delaunay triangulation instead.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "graph-builder-subclassing-squidpy",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "You have spatial molecular data (e.g., coordinates from microscopy or sequencing assays stored in an AnnData object), you need to compute a k-nearest-neighbor graph for spatial statistics (e.g., neighborhood analysis, spatial autocorrelation), and you want to leverage a specializ",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:09:25.345306+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/image-feature-extraction-from-tissue-sections/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Squidpy introduces a new data object, the ImageContainer, which efficiently stores the image with an on-disk/in-memory switch based on xArray and Dask. This object provides a general mapping between pixel coordinates and molecular profiles, enabling analysts to relate image-level observations to omics measurements. Following standard image-based profiling techniques, Squidpy implements a pipeline based on Dask Image and Scikit-image for preprocessing and segmenting images, extracting morphological, texture and deep-learning-powered features.",
      "asbval:note": "Fully supported: paper describes ImageContainer with lazy dask loading, feature extraction pipeline, and integration with AnnData.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "image-feature-extraction-from-tissue-sections",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Extract spatial and morphological features from tissue microscopy images aligned to single-cell spatial transcriptomics data using lazy dask computation, then materialize results into an AnnData object.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:09:44.967444+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/image-feature-extraction-from-tissue-sections/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To enable efficient processing of very large images, this pipeline utilizes lazy loading, image tiling and multiprocessing. The ImageContainer object is a thin wrapper of an xarray.Dataset and provides efficient access to in-memory and on-disk images. On-disk files are loaded lazily using dask, meaning content is only read in memory when requested.",
      "asbval:note": "Fully supported: paper explicitly describes lazy loading and on-disk/in-memory switching via dask.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "image-feature-extraction-from-tissue-sections",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill enables scalable feature discovery from high-resolution tissue images without loading entire images into memory.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:09:44.967444+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/image-feature-extraction-from-tissue-sections/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Squidpy introduces a new data object, the ImageContainer, which efficiently stores the image with an on-disk/in-memory switch based on xArray and Dask. sq.im.ImageContainer(PATH, layer=<str>, lazy=<bool>). Feature extraction can be parallelized by providing n_jobs. The calculated feature matrix is stored in adata[key]. sq.im.calculate_image_features(adata, img, features=<list>, spot_scale=<float>, scale=<float>, key_added=<str>)",
      "asbval:note": "Fully supported: paper names both ImageContainer and calculate_image_features with exact function signatures.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "image-feature-extraction-from-tissue-sections",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
