    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/nearest-neighbor-graph-construction-pynndescent/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To get all spots within a specified radius (in units of the spatial coordinates) from each spot as neighbors, the parameter radius should be used. sq.gr.spatial_neighbors(adata, coord_type=\"generic\", radius=<float>) Finally, it is also possible to compute a neighbor graph based on Delaunay triangulation. sq.gr.spatial_neighbors(adata, coord_type=\"generic\", delaunay=True)",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes spatial_neighbors() function that builds spatial graphs and saves adjacency/distance matrices to sparse arrays (Numpy or Scipy sparse), but does NOT mention pynndescent by name. Paper uses k-nearest neighbors via Scikit-learn (n_neigh parameter) and Delaunay triangulation, not pynndescent. The function does produce sparse matrices as claimed, but the specific tool (pynndescent) is not used or mentioned in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "nearest-neighbor-graph-construction-pynndescent",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Construct k-nearest neighbor graphs from spatial coordinates using pynndescent's approximate nearest neighbor descent algorithm, producing sparse adjacency and distance matrices in CSR format.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:10:12.776201+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/nearest-neighbor-graph-construction-pynndescent/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "pynndescent is not mentioned anywhere in the paper. The paper uses Scikit-learn's k-nearest neighbors search (passage 8: 'it leverages the k-nearest neighbors search from Scikit-learn') and Delaunay triangulation for neighbor graph construction, not pynndescent.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "nearest-neighbor-graph-construction-pynndescent",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "pynndescent: Provides NNDescent class for approximate nearest neighbor search and graph construction via Euclidean metric queries",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:10:12.776201+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/nearest-neighbor-graph-construction-pynndescent/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The function builds a spatial graph and saves its adjacency and weighted adjacency matrices to adata.obsp['spatial_connectivities'] in either Numpy or Scipy sparse arrays. The weights of the weighted adjacency matrix are distances in the case of coord_type = 'generic' and ordinal numbers of hexagonal rings in the case of coord_type = 'grid'. Together with the connectivities, we also provide a sparse adjacency matrix of distances, saved in adata.obsp['spatial_distances']",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly mentions Scipy sparse arrays for storing adjacency and distance matrices.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "nearest-neighbor-graph-construction-pynndescent",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "scipy.sparse: Constructs and manipulates CSR sparse matrices for adjacency and distance outputs",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:10:12.776201+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/nearest-neighbor-graph-construction-pynndescent/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The function builds a spatial graph and saves its adjacency and weighted adjacency matrices to adata.obsp['spatial_connectivities'] in either Numpy or Scipy sparse arrays.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper mentions Numpy as one option for storing sparse arrays but does not detail specific array operations like flattening indices or setting diagonal values. The role is inferred but not explicitly demonstrated in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
