    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/nearest-neighbor-graph-construction-pynndescent/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Squidpy is built on top of Scanpy and Anndata and it relies on several scientific computing libraries in Python, such as Scikit-image, Napari and Dask. Its modularity makes it suitable to be interfaced with a variety of additional tools in the Python data science and machine-learning ecosystem",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Squidpy integrates KNN graph construction (via sq.gr.spatial_neighbors function) into spatial analysis workflows, but does not mention a 'GraphBuilderCSR base class' by name. The paper describes the spatial_neighbors function and its integration but not the internal class structure claimed.",
