    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/sparse-matrix-csr-format-assembly/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper does not mention pynndescent by name. Paper references k-nearest neighbors search from Scikit-learn for generic coordinate types: 'For a fixed number of the closest spots for each spot, it leverages the k-nearest neighbors search from Scikit-learn and n_neigh must be used to set the number of neighbors.' Squidpy uses Scikit-learn's k-NN, not pynndescent.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
