    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/sparse-matrix-csr-format-assembly/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Squidpy is built on top of Scanpy and Anndata and it relies on several scientific computing libraries in Python, such as Scikit-image, Napari and Dask. Its modularity makes it suitable to be interfaced with a variety of additional tools in the Python data science and machine-learning ecosystem.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Squidpy constructs spatial graphs and stores them in sparse format, but does not mention a 'GraphBuilderCSR' base class or explicitly describe the 'build_graph' interface. The paper describes the spatial_neighbors function (sq.gr.spatial_neighbors) which builds spatial graphs, but does not name the internal class structure as 'GraphBuilderCSR'.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41592-021-01358-2",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
